      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="d5d29ac8-15c3-4cc8-9638-089b3f9d2939" type="Verb">
          <Vi>Ép buộc, gây áp lực (lên ai/cái gì)</Vi>
          <En>To exert force or influence to make someone do something, often against their will or better judgment.</En>
          <Example>The manager pressured the team to meet the tight deadline.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="c45fec93-7b85-4936-b25c-6a5bfc41c9f1">
              <Vi>Người thân ép bạn đồng ý một quyết định quan trọng.</Vi>
              <En>A family member pressures you into making a major decision you’re unsure about.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="5c8b01d9-fb28-4008-9734-7808a7b750b8">
              <Vi>Chính phủ gây áp lực lên một quốc gia khác để chấm dứt xung đột.</Vi>
              <En>The government pressures another country to end the conflict.</En>
            </Situation>
          </Situations>
